{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-009__001__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-009", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 1, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·009.1", "chinese_text": "匏有苦葉，濟有深涉，深則厲，淺則揭。", "translation_ref": "匏有苦葉.1", "translation_text": "The gourd has [still] its bitter leaves,\nAnd the crossing at the ford is deep.\nIf deep, I will go through with my clothes on;\nIf shallow, I will do so, holding them up."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-009__002__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-009", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 2, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·009.2", "chinese_text": "有瀰濟盈，有鷕雉鳴，濟盈不濡軓，雉鳴求其牡。", "translation_ref": "匏有苦葉.2", "translation_text": "The ford is full to overflowing;\nThere is the note of the female pheasant.\nThe full ford will not wet the axle of my carriage;\nIt is the pheasant calling for her mate."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-009__003__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-009", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 3, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·009.3", "chinese_text": "雝雝鳴鴈，旭日始旦，士如歸妻，迨冰未泮。", "translation_ref": "匏有苦葉.3", "translation_text": "The wild goose, with its harmonious notes,\nAt sunrise, with the earliest dawn,\nBy the gentleman, who wishes to bring home his bride,\n[Is presented] before the ice is melted."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-009__004__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-009", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 4, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·009.4", "chinese_text": "招招舟子，人涉卬否，人涉卬否，卬須我友。", "translation_ref": "匏有苦葉.4", "translation_text": "The boatman keeps beckoning;\nAnd others cross with him, but I do not.\nOthers cross with him, but I do not; —\nI am waiting for my friend."}
